obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34589)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st November, 1951, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 1461, dated 15th September, 1951, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34589&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Marking of Heavy`
  line `Packages Act, 1951.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34590)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34590&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "heavy package" means a package or other object weighing not less that one metric ton,`
  line `which is equal to one thousand kilogrammes or 2204.6 standard pounds or 26.8 standard maunds;`
  line
  line `(b) "inland water-way" means any canal, river, lake or other navigable water in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34591)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Obligation to mark weight on heavy packages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34591&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Every person consigning a heavy package for`
  line `transport by sea or inland water-way from any place in India shall have marked thereon plainly,`
  line `durably and conspicuously the gross weight of the packages:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases or circumstances specified by rules made under this Act where it`
  line `is difficult to determine the correct weight, only the approximate weight may be so marked.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34592)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Inspectors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1961, s. 2, for sections 4 and 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34592&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Inspectors.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint`
  line `such persons as it thinks fit to be inspectors for the purposes of this Act and assign to each of them one or`
  line `more areas to be specified in the notification, or to two or more of them the same area to be so specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Every inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34593)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1961, s. 2, for sections 4 and 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34593&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Powers of inspectors.--Subject to any rules made by the Central Government in this behalf, an`
  line `inspector appointed under sub-section (1) of section 4 may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter, with such assistants as he considers necessary, and inspect any place or vessel and`
  line `examine any packages found therein;`
  line
  line `(b) if, on such examination, any heavy package is found not to have been marked in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of section 3, direct that the package shall not be transported by sea or inland`
  line `waterway until it has been marked in accordance with those provisions:`
  line
  line `Provided that, instead of issuing any direction as aforesaid, the inspector may himself cause the`
  line `package to be marked in accordance with the provisions of section 3; and in any such case, the expenses`
  line `incurred by him for such marking shall be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue from the person`
  line `consigning the package for transport.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34594)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34594&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person contravenes--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of section 3, or`
  line
  line `(b) any direction given by an inspector under clause (b) of section 5,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person wilfully obstructs an inspector in the exercise of his powers under this Act, he shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34595)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34595&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the person committing an offence under this Act is a`
  line `company, the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the`
  line `conduct of its business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceed against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34596)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34596&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or a Magistrate`
  line `of the first class shall try any offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act except on a complaint in writing`
  line `made by an inspector within six months of the date on which the offence is alleged to have been`
  line committed.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34597)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34597&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34598)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872&sectionId=34598&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00003_195139_1517807322872
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules providing for--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions as to the manner of marking of heavy packages, the manner of their packing`
  line `and the type of covering to be used;`
  line
  line `(b) the cases or circumstances in which the approximate weight of heavy packages instead of`
  line `their correct weight may be marked;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which has to be, or may be, provided for by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the`
  line `session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
